      • WrapLayout

        public WrapLayout()
        Constructs a new WrapLayout with a left alignment and a default 5-unit horizontal and vertical gap.

      • WrapLayout

        public WrapLayout(int align)
        Constructs a new WrapLayout with the specified alignment and a default 5-unit horizontal and vertical gap. The value of the alignment argument must be one of FlowLayout.LEFT, FlowLayout.RIGHT, FlowLayout.CENTER, FlowLayout.LEADING, or FlowLayout.TRAILING.
        Parameters:
        align - the alignment value

      • WrapLayout

        public WrapLayout(int align,
                  int hgap,
                  int vgap)
        Creates a new wrap layout manager with the indicated alignment and the indicated horizontal and vertical gaps.

        The value of the alignment argument must be one of FlowLayout.LEFT, FlowLayout.RIGHT, FlowLayout.CENTER, FlowLayout.LEADING, or FlowLayout.TRAILING.

        Parameters:
        align - the alignment value
        hgap - the horizontal gap between components
        vgap - the vertical gap between components
